http://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis book celebrates the new IFLA School Library Guidelines and shows how the Guidelines can be used in improving school library services. Each chapter describes innovative initiatives for developing, implementing and promoting school library guidelines. The book provides inspiration and guidance for the creation of national school library standards and for the development and use of standards and guidelines to change school library practice, to define the teaching role of school librarians, to guide the initial preparation of school librarians, and to advocate for school library services. Contributors to the book come from around the world: Australia, Canada, Ethiopia, France, Malaysia, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Spain, Sweden and the United States. Their work illustrates the shared commitment of school librarians around the world to "teaching and learning for all", as envisioned in the IFLA/UNESCO School Library Manifesto.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aSchool librariesxAims and objectives. 0aSchool librariesxStandards. 4aSchulbibliothek. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh1 aOberg, Dianne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchultz-Jones, Barbara A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Library and Information Science 2015z9783110438628oZDB-23-DGB0 cEPUBz97831103958530 cprintz978311036243540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311036266440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/97831